### WebSocket Tests for Real-time Tracking
### Note: These are examples of WebSocket connections
### You'll need to use a WebSocket client or browser to test these

### WebSocket Connection URL
### ws://localhost:3000

### Join Tracking Room
### Event: joinTracking
### Payload: { "trackingNumber": "TRK123456789" }
### Headers: { "Authorization": "Bearer {{authToken}}" }

### Listen for Events:
### - locationUpdate: Real-time location changes
### - statusUpdate: Parcel status changes  
### - etaUpdate: Estimated arrival time updates

### Example WebSocket Messages:

### Join tracking room
{
  "event": "joinTracking",
  "data": {
    "trackingNumber": "{{trackingNumber}}"
  }
}

### Leave tracking room
{
  "event": "leaveTracking",
  "data": {
    "trackingNumber": "{{trackingNumber}}"
  }
}

### Expected Response Events:

### Location Update
{
  "event": "locationUpdate",
  "data": {
    "trackingNumber": "TRK123456789",
    "lat": 40.7128,
    "lng": -74.0060,
    "address": "123 Main St, New York, NY",
    "timestamp": "2025-07-27T20:52:36.000Z"
  }
}

### Status Update
{
  "event": "statusUpdate", 
  "data": {
    "trackingNumber": "TRK123456789",
    "status": "IN_TRANSIT",
    "timestamp": "2025-07-27T20:52:36.000Z"
  }
}

### ETA Update
{
  "event": "etaUpdate",
  "data": {
    "trackingNumber": "TRK123456789",
    "estimatedArrival": "2025-07-28T15:00:00.000Z",
    "distance": 2.5,
    "duration": 15
  }
} 